<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<object type="traktor.mcp.SkillAsset">
	<name>add-static-mesh-collider</name>
	<description>Give static/level geometry a concave triangle-mesh collider a character controller respects.</description>
	<whenToUse><![CDATA[Need collision for level/static geometry (maze, terrain, props) from an existing model.]]></whenToUse>
	<body><![CDATA[# Add a static triangle-mesh collider

Give static/level geometry "{{name}}" (built from the model "{{model}}") collision that a physics character controller respects.

## Steps
1. Create `traktor.physics.MeshAsset { fileName: "{{model}}", calculateConvexHull: false, margin: 0 }`.
   - `calculateConvexHull: false` → a **concave triangle mesh** (correct for static level geometry). `true` builds a convex hull (for dynamic/compact bodies only).
   - `build_asset` → a `physics::Mesh` (its guid = the MeshAsset guid).
2. On the entity, add:
   `traktor.physics.RigidBodyComponentData { bodyDesc: traktor.physics.StaticBodyDesc { shape: traktor.physics.MeshShapeDesc { mesh: <physics mesh guid>, collisionGroup: [Default], collisionMask: [Default] } } }`
   - **Default** collision group guid = `{F9805131-50C2-504C-9421-13C99E44616C}`.
3. Keep the visual `traktor.mesh.MeshComponentData` on the same entity (the collider is invisible). Build the scene.

## Gotchas
- The character controller **sweeps against bodies in its `traceInclude` group** — put the collider in the SAME group the controller traces (Default), or the character passes straight through.
- The physics MeshAsset always triangulates internally, so quad geometry is fine.
- One mesh asset serves both purposes: the same source `.tmd` feeds a `mesh.MeshAsset` (visual) and a `physics.MeshAsset` (collision).
]]></body>
	<engineVersion/>
	<published>true</published>
	<parameters>
		<item type="traktor.mcp.SkillParameter">
			<name>name</name>
			<description>Entity name</description>
			<defaultValue>Level</defaultValue>
		</item>
		<item type="traktor.mcp.SkillParameter">
			<name>model</name>
			<description>Source model path (.tmd)</description>
			<defaultValue>Models/Level.tmd</defaultValue>
		</item>
	</parameters>
</object>
